:''For Grant Turner the musician, see [[Grant Turner (musician)]]''.

'''Grant Turner''' (born [[October 7]], [[1958]] in [[New Zealand]]) was a [[football (soccer)]] player who represented [[New Zealand national soccer team|New Zealand]] gaining 71 caps from [[1980]] to [[1988]]<ref>[http://www.nzsoccer.com/page/50_caps_club.html All Whites - 50 Caps Club]</ref><ref name ="1982Allwhites">[http://www.nzsoccer.com/page/1982_world_cup_team.html NZ 1982 World Cup]</ref>
, scoring 19 goals<ref>[http://www.nzsoccer.com/page/goal_scoring_record.html All Whites - Goal Scoring Record]</ref>. A midfielder with an aggressive playing style, Turner was a no nonsense ball winner and runner who had an eye for goal. He was capable of playing in attack if called upon to do so.

Turner was a member of the [[All Whites]] at the [[1982 FIFA World Cup]] in [[Spain]], where they lost all 3 group games to [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]], [[USSR national football team|USSR]] and [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]], but did not play in the finals due to an injury sustained soon avter arrival in Spain.<ref name ="1982Allwhites" />

==Club history==
*[[Gisborne City]] (1980-1984)
*[[Petone (soccer)|Petone]] (1985)
*[[Miramar Rangers]] (1986)
*[[Wellington United]] 


